# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Speed Insights for the K9 Rehab Pro frontend application following the latest official Vercel documentation.

## What Was Done

### 1. Project Analysis
- Identified the project as a **Vite + React** application
- Discovered that `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0` was already listed in package.json but not properly configured in the active entry point
- Found two entry files:
  - `src/index.jsx` (unused, contained Speed Insights setup)
  - `src/main.jsx` (actual entry point referenced in index.html, missing Speed Insights)

### 2. Documentation Review
- Fetched the latest installation instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Confirmed the correct implementation pattern for React applications:
  ```javascript
  import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';
  // Add <SpeedInsights /> component to the app
  ```

### 3. Implementation
**Modified File:**
- `src/main.jsx` - Added Speed Insights component to the correct entry point

**Changes Made:**
1. Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
2. Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<ThemeProvider>` wrapper, after the `<App />` component
3. Followed the official documentation pattern exactly as specified

### 4. Testing & Verification
- ✅ Dependencies verified: `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0` confirmed installed
- ✅ Production build successful: Build completed in 11.10s with no errors
- ✅ Dev server startup: Server started successfully on port 3001
- ✅ No new dependencies added (package was already in package.json)
- ✅ No breaking changes introduced

## Technical Details

**Package Version:** `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0`

**Framework:** Vite + React 19.2.4

**Entry Point:** `src/main.jsx` (referenced in index.html)

**Component Placement:** Inside `<ThemeProvider>` after `<App />`, within `<React.StrictMode>`

## Next Steps for Deployment

To see Speed Insights metrics in your Vercel dashboard:

1. Ensure you have a Vercel account and project set up
2. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Speed Insights)
3. Deploy the application: `vercel deploy`
4. Metrics will appear in the dashboard after user visits (typically within a few days)

## Notes

- No additional configuration is required beyond adding the component
- The SpeedInsights component automatically collects and sends performance metrics to Vercel
- This implementation follows the latest Vercel documentation (v2 package)
- The existing `@vercel/analytics` component continues to work alongside Speed Insights
